Police in Bellville in Cape Town have arrested two men in connection with the murder of an elderly minibus taxi marshall, Western Cape police said on Saturday. Bellville South African Police Service (SAPS) officers arrested the pair when they followed up on information from the public on Friday night, Captain FC van Wyk said. A shooting incident occurred at the Bellville taxi rank on Friday night in which an elderly man who worked as a marshall at the taxi rank was shot dead. Officers who attended the scene received information from the public about two men who fled in a taxi and they immediately followed it up. The officers pursued a Toyota Quantum minibus, pulled it over, and arrested the two suspects. Officers then searched the minibus taxi and found two firearms a .38 special revolver and a 9mm Star pistol with the serial numbers filed off. A case of murder and possession of illegal firearms had been opened. The two suspects would appear in the Bellville Magistrate s Court on Monday, Van Wyk said. African News Agency (ANA) For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter